reviews.review_text: Friendly staff and very knowledgeable in their line of products. They gave us a lot of advices since we were buying seafood to bring to our family who lives oversea. They offered to help us keep them in the tanks until closer to the time we fly and we really appreciated it. Their prices are relatively cheaper than most markets so check it out if you need to buy bulks of seafood.
They have the best seafood and service, the manager will make you satisfied about their products
The only place to get live rock cod. Just bought a 1.5 pound live rock cod from them for dinner. Even tnt did not sell live rock cod.

Seafood is always fresh and staff is always helpful. I always get my tilapia here because they clean it so well. They remove all of the fish guts and bloody stuff for me, just a quick rinse before cooking is a time saver.
They ship out to other smaller Seafood sellers as well; Thus, you know their seafood is always fresh. Great price, fresh items and lots of selection.
The best place to get your spot prawns. When everyone else is over $21/lb, they never hit $20. Bring cash.
Bbq pork is excellent, not salty and is the cheapest in town.

Sells fresh seafood at reasonable prices.  Roast meat is so-so.  Ordered the crispy roast pork and char siu on several occasions and tended  to be drier but price is a few dollars cheaper compared to shops in Richmond.  One thing I must say is that this place doesnt appear to be that clean...there are flies around and a couple of times, I am not sure if staff wash their hands with soap after coming out from the back and then start chopping the BBQ meat.  Decent neighborhood place to get seafood...and perhaps cheaper BBQ meat if you dont mind.
